Assistant Defense Secretary RichardPerle is preparing to announce his resignation from thePentagon, possibly as early as today, Pentagon officials said.    The officials, who asked not to be identified, told Reutersthat Perle was expected to quit in order to become a privatedefense consultant.    Perle, a staunch critic of U.S.-Soviet arms controlagreements and an influential spokesman for anti-Soviethardliners in and out of the Reagan Administration, has servedas assistant defense secretary for international securitypolicy since 1981. Reuter&#3;